 that one was always the<br />"conceptually makes sense" one.<br /><br />So I suspected it would be some low-memory issue and the flag that<br />woudl turn out to matter would be the NOMEMALLOC one, but I'm happy to<br />have been wrong. Adding __GFP_RECLAIMABLE is sane, although I really<br />would like to understand why the i915 driver apparently cares so<br />deeply about the allocation/freeing patterns.<br /><br />But whatever. Thanks again for being such a thorough tester,<br /><br />                        Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
